chatgpt_double_star.new_statement: Laws on abortion should be guided by protecting human dignity on all sides—taking seriously the moral concern many feel for developing life while ensuring pregnant people can obtain timely, medically appropriate care without fear or confusion. A balanced framework can allow access early in pregnancy, set clearer guardrails later that rely on medical standards, and include explicit exceptions for rape, incest, and threats to the patient’s life or serious health. Common ground also means investing in prevention and support—contraception and accurate education, prenatal and postpartum care, and practical help for parenting and adoption—so fewer families face crisis-driven decisions.
